1. Build the docker image from Dockerfile

2. Pushed it into DockerHub repository

3. cd Terraform then do terraform init and terraform apply to create azure kubernetes cluster

4. create a kubernetes secret file to pull image from DockerHub in kubernetes deployment file.

5. link to create the kubernetes secret for DockerHub https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/configure-pod-container/pull-image-private-registry/

6. cd Ansible then do ansible-playbook ansible-playbook.yaml to configure kubernetes cluster to deploy application.